---
import BaseLayout from "~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

export const prerender = true;
const updated = "June 15, 2026";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use — Clad"
  description="The terms governing use of CladFacts (cladfacts.com): editorial commentary, no warranties, fair use."
>
  <article class="static-page">
    <h2 class="static-page__title">Terms of Use</h2>
    <p class="dateline">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <p>
      These Terms govern your use of the website at <strong>cladfacts.com</strong>
      (the "Site"), operated by <strong>CladFacts LLC</strong> ("CladFacts,"
      "Clad," "we," "us"). By using the Site
      you agree to these Terms. If you don't agree, please don't use the Site.
    </p>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">What Clad is</h3>
    <p>
      Clad is an independent political fact-checking publication. Its reports are
      <strong>editorial commentary, opinion, and analysis</strong> of news
      broadcasts and other publicly available material, produced with AI
      assistance and reviewed by a human editor. Letter grades, factuality
      scores, and political-lean ratings assess the <em>evidence and reporting</em>
      in the material reviewed—they are our opinions, not statements of fact about
      the character of any person named. Source material (including short
      quotations and embedded clips) is used for the purposes of commentary and
      criticism under fair use.
    </p>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">No warranties; not professional advice</h3>
    <p>
      The Site and its content are provided <strong>"as is," without warranties
      of any kind</strong>, express or implied. While we strive for accuracy and
      issue corrections, we do not warrant that content is complete, current, or
      error-free. Nothing on the Site is legal, financial, medical, or other
      professional advice. Every report links to its sources; please verify
      independently and form your own conclusions.
    </p>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">Corrections</h3>
    <p>
      When we get something wrong, we issue a correction as a new post rather than
      silently editing the original.
    </p>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">Acceptable use</h3>
    <p>You agree not to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>use the Site for any unlawful purpose;</li>
      <li>attempt to disrupt, overload, or gain unauthorized access to the Site or its systems;</li>
      <li>scrape or harvest the Site in a manner that burdens it or misrepresents its content; or</li>
      <li>republish substantial portions of our content as your own.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">Intellectual property</h3>
    <p>
      The original reports, grades, ratings, and design on the Site are Clad's
      and are protected by intellectual-property laws. Third-party names, logos,
      quotations, and video content remain the property of their respective
      owners and appear here for commentary and identification. You may share
      links to our pages freely.
    </p>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">Third-party content and links</h3>
    <p>
      Reports embed source videos (e.g., from YouTube) and link to outside
      sources. We don't control and aren't responsible for third-party content,
      websites, or their terms and privacy practices.
    </p>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">Limitation of liability</h3>
    <p>
      To the fullest extent permitted by law, Clad will not be liable for any
      indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from your use of, or
      inability to use, the Site or its content.
    </p>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub">Changes</h3>
    <p>
      We may update these Terms as the Site evolves; the "Last updated" date above
      reflects the current version. Continued use after changes means you accept
      them.
    </p>

    <h3 class="static-page__sub" id="contact">Contact</h3>
    <p>
      Questions, or think we got something wrong? Email
      <a href="mailto:support@cladfacts.com">support@cladfacts.com</a>.
    </p>

    <p class="static-page__note">
      These Terms are provided for transparency and are not legal advice.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
